Ok, you left out several items:

gas cable
heat cables
heat tubes that connect to the heat exchangers
wiring
gas line
also, of the four bolts, the two top are removed from inside the engine
compartment for single port; and for dual port, only the driver side from
engine compartment, the other is a bolt from underneath
finally, depending on year, the transmission may need to be supported
seperately

